You can allow Ollama to listen on all network interfaces by setting the environment variable `OLLAMA_HOST` to `0.0.0.0`. 

For example, with Nginx:

```nginx theme={"system"}
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;  # Replace with your domain or IP
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://0.0.0.0:11434;
        proxy_set_header Host 0.0.0.0:11434;
    }
}
```

Alternatively, you can set the environment variable `OLLAMA_HOST` to `0.0.0.0`:

```shell theme={"system"}
export OLLAMA_HOST=0.0.0.0
```

This will allow Ollama to listen on all network interfaces instead of only localhost.
